South Africa's flanker Siya Kolisi (C) lifts the Webb Ellis Cup as they celebrate winning the Japan 2019 Rugby World Cup final match between England and South Africa at the International Stadium Yokohama in Yokohama on November 2, 2019. JOHANNESBURG - The South African World Cup-winning squad and coaches will arrive in Johannesburg from Japan on Tuesday and Wednesday, according to a SA Rugby statement. READ: Erasmus, coach who turned failing Boks into World Cup winners Captain Siya Kolisi and coach Rassie Erasmus are scheduled to return Tuesday evening local time and hold a press conference at OR Tambo airport. A nationwide victory tour will include visits to Johannesburg, Pretoria, Soweto (Thursday), Durban (Friday), East London (Saturday), Port Elizabeth (Sunday) and Cape Town (Monday). IN PICTURES: Springboks show defence wins matches South Africa outplayed pre-match favourites England 32-12 in Yokohama Saturday to join New Zealand as record three-time winners of the World Cup.